    <body>Select the <b class="Bold">Allow Edits to Mobile</b> checkbox to allow the user to add or edit a mobile phone number when SMS text authentication is enabled. This option needs to be enabled if the <a href="../../../../Organization Configuration/Organizations/Signature.htm#ValidateIdentityVerification" target="_blank" alt="Validate Identity Verification">Validate Identity Verification</a> option is enabled in Organization Configuration/Organization Settings/Signature tab. See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Features/SMS Text Authentication.htm" target="_blank" alt="SMS Text Authentication">SMS Text Authentication</MadCap:xref> in Features for more information. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online">See also "SMS Text Authentication" in <MadCap:xref href="../../../../UserGuide/New Activity/Signatures/Client Signature.htm" target="_blank" alt="Client Signature [User Instructions]">Client Signature [User Instructions]</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></body>
